{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7c22598f-f462-4323-b049-5873677857c3","content":"Analyzing crash dumps falls outside the scope of my available tools (the `dump-collect` skill is only for **capturing** dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can investigate your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — cross-platform, .NET-focused\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   # Then run: clrstack, pe (print exception), dumpheap, etc.\n   ```\n\n2. **`lldb`** (Linux/macOS) with the SOS debugging extension\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   # Then: clrstack, pe, dso\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg** (Windows) — full-featured native + managed debugging\n\n### Key Commands (in dotnet-dump or SOS)\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pe` | Print last exception & stack trace |\n| `clrstack -all` | Managed call stacks for all threads |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n\nStart with `pe` — it usually reveals the crash cause immediately.\n\nWould you like help setting up any of these tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e226aac0-7577-4956-a6fa-6026bdcdb3ea","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":446},"id":"c03ef84a-a23d-4d25-95de-63b3603c31e8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:06:03.962Z","parentId":"e1576635-121c-46db-a2c1-bb01c8e02c56"}
